<sect1 id="XMLENCODE">
  <!-- DNT-Start --><title>XMLENCODE</title><!-- DNT-End -->

  <para><emphasis role="bold"><!-- DNT-Start -->XMLENCODE<!-- DNT-End --><indexterm>
      <primary><!-- DNT-Start -->XMLENCODE<!-- DNT-End --></primary>
    </indexterm><indexterm>
      <primary><!-- DNT-Start -->XMLENCODE<!-- DNT-End --> Function</primary>
    </indexterm>(</emphasis><emphasis> xml </emphasis><emphasis
  role="bold">[</emphasis><emphasis>,</emphasis><emphasis role="bold">
  <!-- DNT-Start -->ALL<!-- DNT-End --><indexterm>
      <primary><!-- DNT-Start -->ALL<!-- DNT-End --></primary>
    </indexterm> ] )</emphasis></para>

  <para><informaltable colsep="1" frame="all" rowsep="1">
      <tgroup cols="2">
        <colspec colwidth="77.05pt" />

        <colspec />

        <tbody>
          <row>
            <entry><!-- DNT-Start --><emphasis>xml</emphasis><!-- DNT-End --></entry>

            <entry>The <!-- DNT-Start -->XML<!-- DNT-End --> to encode.</entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry><!-- DNT-Start --><emphasis role="bold">ALL</emphasis><!-- DNT-End --></entry>

            <entry>Optional. Specifies including new line characters in the
            encoding so the text can be used in attribute definitions.</entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry><!-- DNT-Start -->Return:<!-- DNT-End --></entry>

            <entry><!-- DNT-Start -->XMLENCODE<!-- DNT-End --> returns a single value.</entry>
          </row>
        </tbody>
      </tgroup>
    </informaltable></para>

  <para>The <emphasis role="bold"><!-- DNT-Start -->XMLENCODE<!-- DNT-End --></emphasis> function encodes
  special characters in an <!-- DNT-Start -->XML<!-- DNT-End --> string (for example, &lt; is converted to
  &amp;lt) allowing you to use the <!-- DNT-Start -->CSV<!-- DNT-End --> option on <!-- DNT-Start -->OUTPUT<!-- DNT-End --> to produce more
  complex <!-- DNT-Start -->XML<!-- DNT-End --> files than are possible by using the <!-- DNT-Start -->XML<!-- DNT-End --> option.</para>

  <para>Example:</para>

  <!-- DNT-Start --><programlisting>  d := XMLENCODE('&lt;xml version 1&gt;&lt;tag&gt;data&lt;/tag&gt;');
  e := XMLDECODE(d);
</programlisting><!-- DNT-End -->

  <para>See Also: <link linkend="XMLDECODE"><!-- DNT-Start -->XMLDECODE<!-- DNT-End --></link></para>
</sect1>
